What You Must Change in OpenNest
Three things are non-negotiable:
Add a Sunday accountability loop. Every Sunday, active Domain Pod members submit proof of work — GitHub commit, demo link, written update. No proof = marked inactive. This is the missing half of your weekly engine.
Define promotion criteria with numbers. Open Community → Domain Pod: complete 1 assigned entry task within 2 weeks. Domain Pod → Core Council: 3 shipped projects + 1 documented write-up + 1 mentor-reviewed contribution. Hard numbers. No exceptions.
Build the tracking Notion now. Every Domain Pod member: name, domain, active project, deadline, status. You run OpenNest Saturday meetings off this board. No board = no visibility = no accountability.
The fourth thing is important but not urgent: add monthly events. Even one monthly builders session changes the energy of the club significantly.
The rest of your blueprint is structurally solid. The gap isn't vision — it's the operational mechanisms that make the vision real.